value.Title: Skeletal Muscle Oxygen Trnsprt
value.Description: The overall goal of this course is to provide training in critical interpretation of scientific research related to the field of Exercise Physiology. Focus is placed on the regulation of skeletal muscle oxygen transport during the transition from rest to exercise in health and disease. The course is organized in both lecture and seminar format. Learning will be encouraged by the revision, interpretation and group discussions of seminal and recently published original articles selected from top journals in the field.  Course objectives:  1. to provide a foundation in cardiorespiratory and skeletal muscle physiology 2. to understand the physiological changes occurring during acute and chronic exercise in health and disease 3. to study how oxygen is transported to meet the energetic demands of contracting skeletal muscle

value.Title: Science And Business Of Sports
value.Description: This week-long program will take students on a whirlwind tour of an athletics department.  They will have hands-on experiences with key stakeholders and by the end of the week should have a better understanding of the complexities of this department.  There will be an opportunity to learn from members of the sports medicine team including athletic trainers, sports medicine physicians, dieticians, psychologists, and strength and conditioning professionals.  Students will also be exposed to the business of athletics through time with administrators and members of our game day experience team.
